setUp().details: This function: - Deploys the DeCup contract and helper config - Creates mock tokens (WETH, WBTC, USDC) - Funds the test user with initial balances - Transfers mock tokens to the test user

testAddNativeCollateralToExistingCup().details: Verifies that the contract can receive ETH and updates its balance correctly

testAddNativeCollateralToExistingCupAndB.details: Verifies that the contract can receive ETH and updates its balance correctly

testAddTokenCollateralToExistingCup().details: Verifies that the contract can receive ERC20 tokens and updates the collateral balance correctly

testBurnNftWithdrawsNativeCurrency().details: Verifies that burning an NFT minted with native currency deposit returns the correct amount to the user

testBurnNftWithdrawsSingleAsset().details: Verifies that the contract properly handles single asset deposits and withdrawals

testCollateralNftOwner().details: Verifies that the NFT owner is correctly set to the user after depositing native currency

testDeployRevertsWhenPriceFeedAddressesA.details: Verifies the contract correctly enforces non-empty price feed addresses requirement

testDeployRevertsWhenTokenAddressesArray.details: Verifies the contract correctly enforces non-empty token addresses requirement

testDeployRevertsWhenTokenAndPriceFeedAr.details: Verifies the contract correctly enforces matching array lengths requirement for token and price feed addresses

testDepositMultipleAssetsAndMintSuccess(.details: Tests that: - Multiple ERC20 tokens and native currency can be deposited in a single transaction - NFT is minted with correct collateral data - All collateral can be withdrawn by burning the NFT - Final balances match initial balances after full cycle

testDepositMultipleAssetsAndMintTransfer.details: Verifies that the contract properly handles failed token transfers by reverting the transactionUses a mock token configured to fail transfers to simulate the error condition

testDepositSingleAssetZeroAmount().details: Verifies that the contract properly validates non-zero amounts for token deposits

testDepositSingleToken().details: Verifies that the contract properly handles single token deposits and withdrawals

testDepositSingleTokenWithNotAllowedToke.details: Verifies that the contract properly validates that the token is allowed

testDepositdNativeCurrencyMintedTokenURI.details: Verifies that depositing native currency and ERC20 tokens results in the expected tokenURI metadata

testGetAssetTokenIdTCL().details: Verifies that depositing native currency and ERC20 tokens results in the expected TCL

testGetAssetsInfoAfterAddingCollateral().details: Verifies that the function returns updated information after adding more collateral

testGetAssetsInfoMixedAssets().details: Verifies the function behavior with both ERC20 tokens and native currencyThis test will fail due to the bug in the current implementation

testGetAssetsInfoMultipleTokens().details: Verifies that the function returns properly formatted asset information strings for multiple tokens

testGetAssetsInfoNonExistentToken().details: Verifies that the function returns empty array when called with non-existent token ID

testGetAssetsInfoSingleToken().details: Verifies that the function returns properly formatted asset information string

testGetAssetsInfoWithNativeCurrency().details: Verifies that the function reverts when trying to get symbol for address(0) (native currency)This test exposes a bug in the current implementation

testListForSale().details: Verifies that the token is listed for sale after listing

testReceiveNative().details: Verifies the contract can receive ETH and updates its balance correctly

testReceiveNativeZeroAmount().details: Verifies the contract correctly enforces non-zero deposit amount requirement

testRemoveFromSale().details: Verifies that the token is removed from sale after removing

testRevertWhenAddingNotAllowedTokenColla.details: Verifies that the contract properly validates that the token is allowed

testRevertWhenBurningNonExistentNft().details: Verifies that the contract properly validates token existence before burning

testRevertsWhenDepositingEmptyArraysWith.details: Verifies that the contract reverts when attempting to deposit empty arrays without any native currency valueThis test ensures the contract properly validates that at least one form of collateral is provided

testRevertsWhenDepositingMultipleAssetsW.details: Verifies that the contract properly validates that the token addresses and amounts arrays have the same lengthUses a combination of valid and invalid lengths to test the validation logic
Verifies that the contract properly validates non-zero amounts for each token depositUses a combination of valid and zero amounts to test the validation logic

testgetTokenPriceInUsd().details: Verifies that depositing native currency and ERC20 tokens results in the expected TCL

setUp().notice: Sets up the test environment by deploying contracts and initializing test variables

testAddNativeCollateralToExistingCup().notice: Tests that native currency can be added to an existing cup

testAddNativeCollateralToExistingCupAndB.notice: Tests that native currency can be added to an existing cup

testAddTokenCollateralToExistingCup().notice: Tests that token collateral can be added to an existing cup

testBurnNftWithdrawsNativeCurrency().notice: Tests that native currency can be withdrawn by burning the NFT

testBurnNftWithdrawsSingleAsset().notice: Tests that the single asset deposit and withdrawal works correctly

testCollateralNftOwner().notice: Tests that the NFT owner is correctly set to the user

testDeployRevertsWhenPriceFeedAddressesA.notice: Tests that deployment reverts when price feed addresses array is empty

testDeployRevertsWhenTokenAddressesArray.notice: Tests that deployment reverts when token addresses array is empty

testDeployRevertsWhenTokenAndPriceFeedAr.notice: Tests that deployment reverts when token addresses and price feed addresses arrays have different lengths

testDepositMultipleAssetsAndMintSuccess(.notice: Tests successful deposit of multiple assets (ERC20 tokens and native currency) and minting of NFT

testDepositMultipleAssetsAndMintTransfer.notice: Tests that the contract reverts when a token transfer fails during multiple asset deposit

testDepositSingleAssetZeroAmount().notice: Tests that the contract reverts when depositing a single asset with a zero amount

testDepositSingleToken().notice: Tests that depositing a single token and burning works correctly

testDepositSingleTokenWithNotAllowedToke.notice: Tests that depositing a single token with a not allowed token reverts

testDepositdNativeCurrencyMintedTokenURI.notice: Tests that the tokenURI is correctly generated for a native currency deposit

testGetAssetTokenIdTCL().notice: Tests that the TCL is correctly calculated for a native currency deposit

testGetAssetsInfoAfterAddingCollateral().notice: Tests that getAssetsInfo returns correct information after adding collateral

testGetAssetsInfoMixedAssets().notice: Tests that getAssetsInfo with mixed ERC20 and native currency

testGetAssetsInfoMultipleTokens().notice: Tests that getAssetsInfo returns correct information for multiple ERC20 tokens

testGetAssetsInfoNonExistentToken().notice: Tests that getAssetsInfo returns empty array for non-existent token

testGetAssetsInfoSingleToken().notice: Tests that getAssetsInfo returns correct information for single ERC20 token

testGetAssetsInfoWithNativeCurrency().notice: Tests that getAssetsInfo reverts when called with native currency

testListForSale().notice: Tests that the token is listed for sale

testReceiveNative().notice: Tests that native currency can be received by the contract

testReceiveNativeZeroAmount().notice: Tests that native currency deposit reverts when amount is zero

testRemoveFromSale().notice: Tests that the token is removed from sale

testRevertWhenAddingNotAllowedTokenColla.notice: Tests that adding not allowed token collateral to an existing cup reverts

testRevertWhenBurningNonExistentNft().notice: Tests that burning a non-existent NFT reverts with the correct error

testRevertsWhenDepositingEmptyArraysWith.notice: Tests that the contract reverts when depositing empty arrays without native currency

testRevertsWhenDepositingMultipleAssetsW.notice: Tests that the contract reverts when depositing multiple assets with mismatched array lengths
Tests that the contract reverts when depositing multiple assets with a zero amount

testgetTokenPriceInUsd().notice: Tests that the TCL is correctly calculated for a native currency deposit
